What is the remainder when $2001 \cdot 2002 \cdot 2003 \cdot 2004 \cdot 2005$ is divided by 19?
inference:
We want to find the remainder when $2001 \cdot 2002 \cdot 2003 \cdot 2004 \cdot 2005$ is divided by 19.
We can use modular arithmetic. We want to find
$$2001 \cdot 2002 \cdot 2003 \cdot 2004 \cdot 2005 \pmod{19}.$$
We have
$2001 = 19 \cdot 105 + 6$, so $2001 \equiv 6 \pmod{19}$.
$2002 = 19 \cdot 105 + 7$, so $2002 \equiv 7 \pmod{19}$.
$2003 = 19 \cdot 105 + 8$, so $2003 \equiv 8 \pmod{19}$.
$2004 = 19 \cdot 105 + 9$, so $2004 \equiv 9 \pmod{19}$.
$2005 = 19 \cdot 105 + 10$, so $2005 \equiv 10 \pmod{19}$.
Thus,
$$2001 \cdot 2002 \cdot 2003 \cdot 2004 \cdot 2005 \equiv 6 \cdot 7 \cdot 8 \cdot 9 \cdot 10 \pmod{19}.$$
$$6 \cdot 7 \cdot 8 \cdot 9 \cdot 10 = 42 \cdot 72 \cdot 10 = 3024 \cdot 10 = 30240.$$
$$30240 = 19 \cdot 1591 + 11.$$
Thus $30240 \equiv 11 \pmod{19}$.
Therefore, the remainder when $2001 \cdot 2002 \cdot 2003 \cdot 2004 \cdot 2005$ is divided by 19 is 11.

Final Answer: $\boxed{11}$
ground_truth: Reducing each factor modulo 19 first, we see that $2001 \cdot 2002 \cdot 2003 \cdot 2004 \cdot 2005 \equiv 6 \cdot 7 \cdot 8 \cdot 9 \cdot 10 \equiv 30240 \equiv \boxed{11} \pmod{19}$.
